ypes.go` - Main domain types for evolution system\n- `fitness.go` - Fitness evaluation and Pareto front computation\n- `population.go` - Population management for candidate variants\n- `selector.go` - Candidate selection strategies\n\n**Evolution Pipeline Components:**\n- `collector.go` - Gathers data needed for evolution analysis\n- `classifier.go` - Categorizes runs (bug, feedback, feature, enhancement, chore)\n- `reflector.go` - Examines execution traces and extracts lessons\n- `curator.go` - Merges lessons into prompt files using ACE principles\n- `scriptgen.go` - LLM-based script generation for new steps\n- `orchestrator.go` - Wires all evolution stages together\n\n**Utilities:**\n- `audit.go` - Records evolution actions and manages snapshots\n- `trigger.go` - Debounces evolution pipeline runs per project+workflow\n- `llmclient.go` - LLM client interface\n\n**Test Files:**\n- `types_test.go`, `fitness_test.go`, `population_test.go`, `selector_test.go`\n- `trigger_test.go`, `scriptgen_test.go`, `evolution_test.go`, `corruption_test.go`\n\n---\n\n### 2. Core Types Defined in the Package\n\n#### **Candidate & Fitness Types**\n\nFrom `types.go`:\n- `Candidate` - Prompt variant in GEPA population with ID, PromptID, Content, Generation, ParentID, and FitnessScores\n- `FitnessScores` - Multi-objective fitness with Scores map, Total, Count, and Average\n- `RunScoreRecord` - Simple score outcome: CandidateID, RunID, Score, Details\n- `PopulationConfig` - Configuration for GEPA-style population evolution with Enabled, MaxCandidates, MinRunsToPromote\n\nFrom `fitness.go`:\n- `FitnessRecord` - Metrics from run evaluation: RunID, WorkflowName, Candidate, Success, RetryCount, Duration, Timestamp\n- `CandidateFitness` - Aggregated fitness across runs: Candidate, SuccessRate, Efficiency, RunCount\n- **Pareto Front Functions:**\n  - `Dominates(a, b CandidateFitness) bool` - Returns true if a dominates b in multi-objective comparison\n  - `ComputeParetoFront(candidates []CandidateFitness) []CandidateFitness` - Returns non-dominated set\n\n#### **Population Management Types**\n\nFrom `population.go`:\n- `Population` - Manages candidate prompt variants per step with ProjectDir and StepName\n- `CandidateMeta` - JSONL entry with ID, Status (active/archived/promoted), CreatedAt, ParentID, Score\n- `Assignment` - Maps workflow run to candidate used with RunID, CandidateID, AssignedAt\n\nDisk layout:\n```\n.cloche/evolution/population/<step-name>/\n  candidate-001.md\n  candidate-002.md\n  meta.jsonl\n  assignments.jsonl\n```\n\n#### **Evolution Pipeline Types**\n\nFrom `types.go`:\n- `CollectedData` - Input to Classifier and Reflector with Runs, Captures, KnowledgeBase, CurrentPrompts, CurrentWorkflow, etc.\n- `Lesson` - Structured insight with ID, Category (prompt_improvement/new_step), StepType, Target, Insight, SuggestedAction, Evidence[], Confidence\n- `EvolutionResult` - Records evolution pass output with ID, ProjectDir, WorkflowName, TriggerRunID, Timestamp, Classification, Changes[], KnowledgeDelta\n- `Change` - Single file modification with Type, File, Reason, Snapshot\n\n#### **Other Key Types**\n\n- `Classifier` - Has LLM interface\n- `Reflector` - Has LLM and MinConfidence fields\n- `Curator` - Has LLM and AuditLogger for ACE-style curation\n- `ScriptGenerator` - LLM-based script generation\n- `Orchestrator` - Wires all stages together\n- `LLMClient` interface - `Complete(ctx context.Context, systemPrompt, userPrompt string) (string, error)`\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing Test Patterns\n\n**Test Helper Pattern:**\n```go\nfunc newTestPopulation(t *testing.T) *Population {\n    t.Helper()\n    return &Population{\n        ProjectDir: t.TempDir(),\n        StepName:   \"code\",\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Table-Driven Tests:**\n- Used extensively in `fitness_test.go`, `selector_test.go`\n- Consistent structure with `name`, input fields, expected fields\n- Tests organized in `for _, tt := range tests { t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) { ... }) }`\n\n**Test Organization:**\n- Test files use `package evolution` (not `evolution_test` subpackage), except `fitness_test.go` uses `package evolution_test`\n- Uses `testify/require` and `testify/assert` for assertions\n- `t.TempDir()` for filesystem operations\n\n**Common Test Patterns:**\n- JSON marshaling/unmarshaling tests\n- Disk layout verification\n- Error case handling (NotFound, Invalid, etc.)\n- Behavior verification (e.g., distribution tests for selection strategies)\n\n**Notable Test Files:**\n- `fitness_test.go` - Tests Pareto front computation with complex multi-objective scenarios\n- `population_test.go` - Tests JSONL read/write, file layout, promotion workflow\n- `selector_test.go` - Tests 70/30 split distribution (1000+ iteration sampling)\n- `evolution_test.go` (40KB) - Large integration test with fakeLLM stub\n\n---\n\n### 4. Go Conventions Used in This Project\n\n**Error Handling:**\n- `fmt.Errorf(\"context: %w\", err)` for error wrapping (Go 1.13+)\n- Functions return `(T, error)` tuple\n- Error wrapping with format verbs for context propagation\n- Example: `return \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"reading target prompt %s: %w\", lesson.Target, err)`\n\n**Naming Conventions:**\n- Receiver methods: `(c *Curator)`, `(p *Population)`, `(o *Orchestrator)`\n- Interface names: `LLMClient`, `Classifier`, `Reflector` (noun-like)\n- Unexported helpers: `lessonAlreadyPresent`, `promptSanityCheck`, `stripCodeFences`\n- Constants for status: `candidateStatusActive`, `candidateStatusArchived`, `candidateStatusPromoted`\n\n**File Organization:**\n- One main struct/concept per file (e.g., `population.go`, `fitness.go`, `curator.go`)\n- Type definitions at the top of files\n- Helper/internal functions after main implementations\n- Tests in adjacent `*_test.go` files\n\n**Context Usage:**\n- `ctx context.Context` as first parameter in async/blocking operations\n- Example: `Complete(ctx context.Context, systemPrompt, userPrompt string) (string, error)`\n\n**JSON Handling:**\n- `json: